      "item2": {
        "tag": "[Health Notice]",
        "title": "[Health Notice] High summer temperatures are here, please pay extra attention to the hydration of [elders/patients]",
        "previewDesc": "- Thank you for your hard work: Temperatures have been rising continuously recently. Because [elders/severe patients] often have a dull sense of thirst or poor expression...",
        "time": "10:00 AM",
        "content": "Thank you for your hard work, colleagues:\n\nTemperatures have been rising continuously recently. Because [elders/severe patients] often have a dull sense of thirst or cannot express it clearly, which can easily lead to dehydration or heatstroke risks, please strengthen care according to the following principles:\n\n1. Provide warm water at regular intervals and record daily water intake.\n2. Pay attention to indoor temperature and ventilation, and adjust air conditioning settings if necessary.\n3. If early signs of dehydration such as reduced urine output or dry skin are observed, please intervene early.\n\nPrevention is better than cure, please pay close attention.\n[Publish Date] 2026-06-29"
      },
      "item3": {
        "tag": "[Care Notice]",
        "title": "[Care Notice] Please ensure the implementation of the \"Five Major Fall Prevention Inspections\" and utilize the platform to report environmental hazards in real-time",
        "previewDesc": "- Hello colleagues: Recently, the fall risk assessment index for [residents/patients] on each floor has...",
        "time": "08:42 AM",
        "content": "Hello colleagues:\n\nRecently, the fall risk assessment index for [residents/patients] on various floors has changed. To ensure the safety of individuals, all frontline care staff must implement the following fall prevention inspections after each shift handover:\n\n1. Bedside safety check: Please confirm that when [residents/patients] are out of bed or in bed, the bed rails are securely pulled up, the bed wheels are locked, and the bed exit alarm is functioning properly.\n\n2. Environmental inspection: If you find stagnant water in the aisles, dim lighting, or loose barrier-free handrails, please take photos immediately and report them by uploading them through the platform's \"Logistics Repair/Environmental Report\" section so that the General Affairs team can repair them promptly.\n\n3. Platform assessment sync update: For high-risk individuals, please update the latest data in the \"Fall Risk Assessment Form\" within the platform on the scheduled weekly assessment day, so that the relieving staff can grasp the latest prevention priorities.\n\nFall prevention is everyone's responsibility. A little more attention means a little less regret.\n[Publish Date] 2026-06-29"
      }
    }
